<p class="MsoNormal">For a company that produces real products, like Apple, once the market is saturated with the iPhone 5, you bring out the iPhone 6 and the whole cycle starts again.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">In a world saturated with Debt 1, the banks need to come up with a new product, Debt 2.</p>
<p>I don’t think it exists.</p>
